The '''SNP Stadium''' ({{lang-sk|Štadión SNP, Štiavničky}}) is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Banská Bystrica]], [[Slovakia]]. It is currently used mostly for [[Association football|football]] matches and was the home ground of [[FK Dukla Banská Bystrica]] until the club was dissolved in 2017. The stadium has a capacity of 10,000, with 7,380 seats.

