{{more citations needed|date=August 2011}} {{Infobox football club | clubname = Sugar Boys FC | image = Sugar Boys.png | image_size = 200px | fullname = Sugar Boys Football Club | nickname = | founded =2007 | ground =Shirley Recreation Ground, [[Road Town]] | capacity = 2,000 | chrtitle = | chairman = | mgrtitle = Manager | manager = | league = [[British Virgin Islands Championship|BVIFA Football League]] | season = [[2016–17 BVIFA Football League|2016–17]] | position = 2nd | current = | website =
}}
'''Sugar Boys FC''' is a [[British Virgin Islands]] football club based in [[Virgin Gorda]], competing in the [[British Virgin Islands Championship|BVIFA Football League]], the top tier of [[Football in the British Virgin Islands|British Virgin Islands football]].
Sugar Boys finished second in the 2010–11 season.<ref>{{cite web|last=King|first=Ian|title=British Virgin Islands 2010/11: BVIFA Football League 2010/11|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/brmaagd2011.html#natvg|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]|accessdate=9 August 2011|author2=Karel Stokkerman |date=31 March 2011}}</ref> Sugar Boys also finished second in the 2011-12 season <ref>{{cite web|last=King|first=Ian|title=British Virgin Islands 2011/12: BVIFA Football League 2010/11|url=https://int.soccerway.com/national/british-virgin-islands/bvifa-football-league/20112012/regular-season/r17451/=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]|accessdate=9 August 2011|author2=Karel Stokkerman |date=31 March 2011}}</ref> on both occasions the Islanders team were victors.
==Achievements== *'''[[BVIFA National League]]: 1''' ::2015-16. *'''[[BVIFA Presidents Cup]]: Winners''' ::2016-17. The Sugar Boys put the disappointment of losing out on the 2016-17 National League Championship by beating the Islanders 1-0, to win the Presidents Cup in front of a packed vociferous crowd at the A.O. Shirley Ground on Sunday 12 February 2017.
